        {
            "_id": "YmwKItzUHtPCkXjV",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Soul Shriek",
            "sort": 1600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The vinlach's dozens of mouths suddenly shriek in terrifying unison, yet the sound created is not one that can be heard by ears—rather, it's heard by a living creature's soul, as the supernatural sound attempts to rip free the very animus of life. All creatures in a @Template[type:cone|distance:40] take @Damage[9d6[spirit]|options:area-damage] damage and must attempt a @Check[will|dc:26] save with the following results. The vinlach can't Soul Shriek again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Soul Shriek]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage. If the creature can cast divine spells or has the holy trait, it's also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage. If the creature can cast divine spells or has the holy trait, it's also stupefied 1 for 24 hours.</p>"
                },
